Fifty Shades, book 3 : Fifty shades freed [English] by E.L JAMES

   Summary :

       Ana and Christian couldn't be happier : they just get married !
   They are in honeymoon ! Ana learns to live in Christian's world and he
   does his best to control his obsession... But danger is never far...
   And they worst nightmars become reality...

   What will it happen ?


   Opinion :

        I want to read it, but weirdly I wasn't really hurry to begin
   it... The second book was a big crush, however the end haven't a lot of
   suspens... So the desire was not strong enough to begin it immediatly !
   To be honest, I don't really like this last book... I'm far away of a
   big crush... Already, from the first pages, I was desapointed : we
   don't assist to their wedding ! I wanted to see it !


       After that, the story is good, but I don't know... The suspens was
   not really here and the plot was rather obvious... I mean a Baby ! It
   was a foregone conclusion ! Of course, it was interest, but my
   enthousiasm was not really here... I don't know if it was because I
   read it in English and not in French... We will see that when I will
   read it again in French !


        A other problem was the characters... I love Ana & Christian, but
   I haven't see again their complicity and all the efforts they could do
   for their love... I mean, I feel like their relation doesn't evolve
   since the last book... Except maybe, after the car's accidents... I
   miss their friends too... I find they are not really present, it's too
   bad...


   Good, but no more...


